# Paperless Skill

Use the managed Paperless handler with deterministic read-only commands.

## Input Contract

User input is everything after `/{{ openclaw_paperless_command_skill_name }}`.

- `search <query> [--from YYYY-MM-DD] [--to YYYY-MM-DD] [--limit N]`
- `get <document_id> [--original|--archived]`
- `latest [--query <text>] [--days N] [--limit N]`

Natural-language mapping:

- "letter from AOK last month" -> `search aok letter --from <start_of_last_month> --to <end_of_last_month> --limit 5`
- If exactly one result is a clear match, run `get <document_id>` (defaults to original file).
- For requests like "zeig mir das", "öffne", or "schick das Dokument", prefer `get <document_id>` (original default) for best readability.
- Use `--archived` only when explicitly requested or when troubleshooting a problematic original file.
- If multiple plausible results remain, return the shortlist and ask for an explicit id.

## Execution Rules

Always execute exactly one command:

```bash
{{ openclaw_paperless_container_skills_dir }}/{{ openclaw_paperless_skill_name }}/handler.py <raw-user-input>
```

Execution safety assumption: OpenClaw must pass this invocation as argv arguments (no shell string interpolation).

When no input is provided, return:

`Usage: /{{ openclaw_paperless_command_skill_name }} search <query> [--from YYYY-MM-DD] [--to YYYY-MM-DD] [--limit N] | /{{ openclaw_paperless_command_skill_name }} get <document_id> [--original|--archived] | /{{ openclaw_paperless_command_skill_name }} latest [--query <text>] [--days N] [--limit N]`

Return the handler output as-is.

When you summarize success to the user, mention that the original file was used by default and that `--archived` is available if needed.
